"text": "In addition to the above non-GAAP measures, we use total debt to adjusted earnings before interest, tax, depreciation and amortization (adjusted", "bbox": [125.0, 1180.6, 1146.3, 1203.1]}, {"text": "EBITDA) as a measure of leverage. We define adjusted EBITDA as net income plus expenses of interest, income taxes, depreciation and amortiza-", "bbox": [125.0, 1203.0, 1143.4, 1225.5]}, {"text": "tion, special charges and loss on voluntary pension settlement. Adjusted EBITDA and the ratio of total debt to adjusted EBITDA are both non-GAAP", "bbox": [125.0, 1225.3, 1143.1, 1247.9]}, {"text": "financial measures. This ratio measures our ability to repay outstanding debt obligations. Our target for total debt to adjusted EBITDA is 1.5 to 1.8.", "bbox": [125.0, 1247.7, 1148.9, 1270.3]}, {"text": "Our total debt to adjusted EBITDA can be temporarily impacted by our acquisition activity. We believe that total debt to adjusted EBITDA is a", "bbox": [125.0, 1270.1, 1138.0, 1292.7]}, {"text": "meaningful metric to investors in evaluating our financial leverage and may be different than the method used by other companies to calculate", "bbox": [125.0, 1292.5, 1149.3, 1315.1]}, {"text": "total debt to adjusted EBITDA.", "bbox": [125.0, 1314.9, 337.3, 1337.5]}]}